cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.COMM, cs.SY, cs.MM

The paper discusses the design and evaluation of multiple access schemes for next-generation wireless networks, which is a topic related to network infrastructure and communication technologies. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also involves information theory and signal processing techniques, which suggest possible categories of cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.COMM (Communications and Networking). The evaluation of the schemes using simulations and system-level tools may also relate to cs.SY (Systems and Control) and cs.MM (Multimedia).
